  "panels": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "type": "text",
      "title": "About this dashboard",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 6,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 0
      },
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "**Demo B — Regional Failure + Capacity Injection**\n\n**Important:** open this dashboard on **rp-gcp** or **rp-azure** Grafana. rp-aws Grafana goes dark the moment AWS is cordoned — its Prometheus pods are unreachable too. The surviving cloud's Prometheus keeps scraping its local brokers, and the cluster-wide gauges (broker count, under-replicated partitions, unavailable partitions) are reported by every broker, so any surviving Prometheus sees them correctly.\n\n**Reading the legends — pod names tell you the cloud.** Per-broker series are labeled with pod names (`redpanda-rp-aws-0/1`, `redpanda-rp-gcp-0/1`, `redpanda-rp-azure-0`); the cloud is in the name. Each Prometheus only scrapes its own cloud's brokers, so on rp-gcp Grafana you'll see `redpanda-rp-gcp-*` series and watch new pods (`redpanda-rp-gcp-2`, `redpanda-rp-gcp-3`) appear when the NodePool patch lands.\n\nExpected timeline (≈30 min total):\n1. **T0 — cordon AWS + delete pods.** Broker count drops from 5 → 3. Under-replicated partitions spike (every RF=5 topic loses 2 replicas). Unavailable partitions stays 0 (quorum holds across racks).\n2. **T+10 min — autobalancer stalls.** `node_availability_timeout` fires; autobalancer flags AWS brokers unavailable but has nowhere to put their replicas yet.\n3. **T+10 min — patch rp-gcp NodePool 2 → 4.** Two new broker pods (IDs 5, 6) come up on the new GCP nodes. Watch *Disk free per broker* — the new brokers start with full disks, then fill as replicas land on them.\n4. **T+15 min — autodecom fires.** Brokers 0, 1 (AWS) get auto-decommissioned. *Cluster broker count* climbs back to 5. *Partitions moving to/from* spikes during reassignment, then drains. *Under-replicated partitions* drains to 0.\n5. **T+25 min — uncordon AWS.** Broker count climbs to 7 (AWS brokers re-join as new IDs 7, 8 — they were decommissioned, can't reclaim 0/1).\n6. **T+30 min — patch rp-gcp NodePool back to 2.** Operator decommissions brokers 5, 6 gracefully. Broker count returns to 5.\n\nIf *Storage health alert* turns yellow/red, that's the original Demo B blocker — out-of-disk on a surviving broker. The committed manifests pin PVC size to 200 Gi + `log_retention_ms=3600000` (1h) to keep the demo runnable; if you've changed those, the alert may fire."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Cluster broker count (cluster-wide)",
      "description": "max(redpanda_cluster_brokers) — reported identically by every broker, so safe to read from any surviving cloud's Prometheus. Watch it dip from 5 → 3 at cordon, climb to 5 after GCP scale-up + autodecom, jump to 7 at AWS uncordon, return to 5 after the GCP drain.",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 9,
        "w": 12,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 6
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "max(redpanda_cluster_brokers)",
          "legendFormat": "brokers",
          "refId": "A"
        }
      ],
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "none",
          "min": 0,
          "custom": {
            "drawStyle": "line",
            "lineWidth": 2,
            "fillOpacity": 15,
            "showPoints": "auto"
          },
          "thresholds": {
            "mode": "absolute",
            "steps": [
              {
                "color": "red",
                "value": null
              },
              {
                "color": "yellow",
                "value": 4
              },
              {
                "color": "green",
                "value": 5
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "legend": {
          "displayMode": "list",
          "placement": "bottom"
        },
        "tooltip": {
          "mode": "single"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Under-replicated partitions (cluster-wide)",
      "description": "sum(redpanda_kafka_under_replicated_replicas). Spikes at cordon (every RF=5 topic loses 2 replicas), drains to 0 after autodecom + reassignment.",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 9,
        "w": 12,
        "x": 12,
        "y": 6
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "sum(redpanda_kafka_under_replicated_replicas)",
          "legendFormat": "URP",
          "refId": "A"
        }
      ],
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "none",
          "min": 0,
          "custom": {
            "drawStyle": "line",
            "lineWidth": 2,
            "fillOpacity": 15,
            "showPoints": "auto"
          },
          "thresholds": {
            "mode": "absolute",
            "steps": [
              {
                "color": "green",
                "value": null
              },
              {
                "color": "yellow",
                "value": 1
              },
              {
                "color": "red",
                "value": 20
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "legend": {
          "displayMode": "list",
          "placement": "bottom"
        },
        "tooltip": {
          "mode": "single"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Disk free per broker (this cloud, MB)",
      "description": "redpanda_storage_disk_free_bytes per broker. If any line dives toward 0, you've hit the original Demo B blocker — replicas can't move to a broker that's already full. Committed PVC size is 200 Gi + log_retention 1h.",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 9,
        "w": 12,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 15
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "redpanda_storage_disk_free_bytes / 1024 / 1024",
          "legendFormat": "{{pod}}",
          "refId": "A"
        }
      ],
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "decmbytes",
          "min": 0,
          "custom": {
            "drawStyle": "line",
            "lineWidth": 2,
            "fillOpacity": 10,
            "showPoints": "never"
          }
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "legend": {
          "displayMode": "table",
          "placement": "right",
          "calcs": [
            "lastNotNull",
            "min"
          ]
        },
        "tooltip": {
          "mode": "multi",
          "sort": "asc"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Disk used % per broker (this cloud)",
      "description": "(total - free) / total × 100. Watch new GCP brokers (IDs 5, 6) climb from ~0% as replicas land on them.",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 9,
        "w": 12,
        "x": 12,
        "y": 15
